E. CUSTOMER PRIVACY POLICY
We are constantly believing in the Truth. and in the closest possible Fair Situation for Everyone. To not be cases of bad behavior. or trying to use someone or somehow something to gain a small win over a fair, true, and happy ending. So, If you have already ordered ikigaiAir for a while, or right Now. We don’t sell your personal information, but we still have to tell you what we collect from you when you access or use our websites and how we use it. (We may update this policy from time to time.) Your continued use of this site indicates your agreement with the updated terms.

a. What Personal Information do we collect?
Depending on how you interact with our website, we may collect the following personal information about you, which we have grouped as follows:

• Identity Data, which may include your first name, last name, and title.
• Contact Data, which may include your postal address, email address, and telephone numbers.
• Financial Data, which may include your payment card details and billing address.
• Profile Data, which may include username and password, purchases made by you, and
customer service requests.
• Technical Data, which includes your internet protocol (IP) address, browser type, and version,
time zone setting and location, browser plug-in types and versions, and operating system and
platform.
• Usage Data, which includes information about how you use our website.
• Marketing and Communications Data, which includes your preferences in receiving marketing
and non-marketing communications from us.
• Employment Data – if you apply for employment with ikigaiAir. we will collect your employment
and work history, as well as personal information related to your potential employment. This
may include your education and employment history, address and contact information,
demographic information, and any other information included in your resume or application.

b. How do we collect personal information?
We may collect personal information about you from the following sources:

From you, such as when you subscribe to our publications, purchase an item, request
marketing to be sent to you, enter a promotion, complete a survey, or correspond with us through any
means. As you interact with our website, app, and ecosystem, we will also automatically collect Technical Data about your equipment, browsing actions, and patterns. We collect this personal data by using cookies, server logs, and other similar technologies. 02 Publicly available sources, such as information that you or your organization make publicly available online.


